@startuml
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam backgroundColor #fcfcfd
skinparam defaultFontName Helvetica
skinparam defaultFontSize 14
skinparam arrowColor #0f172a
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #fff7d6
skinparam noteBorderColor #b45309
skinparam noteFontColor #334155
skinparam roundcorner 16
title Activity - rover/RoverNode
skinparam activity {
  backgroundColor #f8fafc
  borderColor #0f172a
  fontColor #0f172a
  diamondBackgroundColor #e2e8f0
  diamondBorderColor #1d4ed8
  diamondFontColor #0f172a
  startColor #1d4ed8
  endColor #0f172a
  barColor #1d4ed8
}
start
partition "Observe and Bind" {
:Start from shared flow\nshared/diagrams/shared-reconcile-activity.svg;
:Read desired RoverNode spec, tracked status,\nand delete intent;
if ("Tracked or explicit OCI identity present?") then (yes)
:Get the current OCI resource via GetRoverNode;
else (no)
:Resolve an existing OCI resource through\nListRoverNodes using filters compartmentId,\ndisplayName, shape;
:Create the OCI resource via CreateRoverNode\nwhen no reusable match is found;
:Persist the resolved or created OCI identity\ninto status;
endif
}
if ("Delete requested?") then (yes)
partition "Delete" {
:Delete path uses DeleteRoverNode with required\nvia GetRoverNode or ListRoverNodes to DELETED,\nNOT_FOUND confirmation;
:Confirm deletion via GetRoverNode or\nListRoverNodes until OCI reaches DELETED,\nNOT_FOUND;
if ("Delete cleanup and finalizer release succeed?") then (yes)
:Remove the finalizer after delete completion;
else (no)
:Stay blocked until cleanup or finalizer\nrelease succeeds;
endif
}
stop
else (no)
partition "Lifecycle Classification" {
if ("OCI state in retryable set?") then (yes)
:Request requeue while OCI remains in CREATING,\nUPDATING, DELETING;
stop
endif
if ("OCI state is outside success targets?") then (yes)
:Return an unsuccessful reconcile result until\nOCI reaches ACTIVE;
stop
endif
}
partition "Ready and Drift Handling" {
:Compare live OCI state against the\nrepo-authored mutation surface;
if ("Force-new or conflicting drift detected?") then (yes)
:Reject drift before OCI mutation for force-new\nfields compartmentId, masterKeyId;
stop
endif
if ("Supported mutable drift detected?") then (yes)
:Apply ChangeRoverNodeCompartment,\nUpdateRoverNode only for mutable fields\ncertCompartmentId, certKeyAlgorithm,\ncertSignatureAlgorithm, certificateAuthorityId\n(+25 more);
else (no)
:Skip the no-op mutation path;
endif
:Run provider helper hooks\ncreate=tfresource.CreateResource;\nupdate=tfresource.UpdateResource;\ndelete=tfresource.DeleteResource when the\nmatching field-driven path executes;
:Return success for the ACTIVE success state;
:Project required status and finalizer policy\nretain-until-confirmed-delete;
:Requeue on provisioning, updating, terminating;
}
endif
stop
note right
shared diagram:
shared/diagrams/shared-reconcile-activity.svg
Start from the shared reconcile activity and
specialize provider-backed CRUD, wait, and
status-projection details here.
Controller-local activity diagrams add
list-lookup hints, secret policies, delete
handling, and open formal gaps.
archetype batch: Generated service-manager
controllers specialize the shared reconcile path
with formal runtime ownership.
service: rover
slug: rovernode
kind: RoverNode
archetype: generated-service-manager
status/finalizer: required /
retain-until-confirmed-delete
requeue: provisioning, updating, terminating
provider states: create CREATING; update
UPDATING; delete DELETING
supported drift: certCompartmentId,
certKeyAlgorithm, certSignatureAlgorithm,
certificateAuthorityId (+25 more)
reject before mutate: force-new fields
compartmentId, masterKeyId
create-only fields: none
list lookup: oci_rover_rover_nodes filters
compartmentId, displayName, shape; exact
compartmentId plus displayName plus shape list
filters with nodeType fixed to STANDALONE, then
exact serialNumber unique match in ACTIVE,
CREATING, or UPDATING summaries only when the
desired serialNumber is non-empty; duplicate
matches fail
conflicts: none
open gaps: none
Reviewed lifecycle mapping treats CREATING as
provisioning, UPDATING as updating, ACTIVE as
success, FAILED as terminal without requeue, and
delete confirmation as DELETING until DELETED or
NotFound.
The published runtime removes
ChangeRoverNodeCompartment from the generated
auxiliary surface and never polls Rover work
requests for CRUD because RoverNode write
responses do not expose opc-work-request-id and
Rover's service-local work-request enum only
documents ADD_NODES.
Pre-create lookup lists by compartmentId,
displayName, and shape with nodeType fixed to
STANDALONE, then narrows returned summaries in
memory with exact serialNumber matching only
when the desired serialNumber is non-empty.
lifecycleState is intentionally omitted from the
list request.
LifecycleState, LifecycleStateDetails,
SystemTags, and nodeWorkloads.workRequestId
remain provider-managed request-shape fields.
The reviewed runtime normalizes them out before
parity or write calls.
Required status projection keeps the OCI body
surface except excluded credential-like fields
and one-time URLs/codes dataValidationCode,
imageExportPar, returnShippingLabelUri,
superUserPassword, and unlockPassphrase. The
runtime has no secret side effects.
end note
@enduml
